P1.12 Auto Scaling Implementation

Changes made:
- Added github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/applicationautoscaling dependency
- Extended deployInput struct with 4 new fields: MinCount, MaxCount, TargetCPUPercent, TargetMemPercent
- Created scalingInfo struct for status reporting
- Added validateAutoScalingParams() with validation per spec:
  * min_count >= 1
  * max_count >= min_count
  * target_cpu_percent between 10-90
  * target_memory_percent between 10-90
  * Warning (not error) for max_count > 10

Implementation details:
- configureAutoScaling() registers ECS service as scalable target
- Creates 2 target tracking policies (CPU and Memory)
- Cooldowns: 60s scale-out (react fast), 300s scale-in (avoid thrashing)
- deleteAutoScaling() cleans up policies then deregisters target
- getScalingInfo() retrieves config from AWS for status reporting

Integration:
- deploy() calls configureAutoScaling when max_count > desired_count
- teardown() calls deleteAutoScaling BEFORE deleting ECS service
- status() includes scaling info when configured

Testing:
- TestValidateAutoScalingParams: 9 test cases
- TestExtractClusterName: 4 test cases
- TestExtractServiceName: 4 test cases
- TestDeployInput_AutoScalingDefaults: verifies struct fields
- TestStatusOutput_ScalingInfo: verifies JSON serialization
- TestStatusOutput_NoScaling: verifies omitempty

Why auto-scaling matters:
- Enables cost-efficient scaling based on actual load
- Protects against traffic spikes by scaling out quickly
- Avoids over-provisioning during low traffic periods
- Required by ralph/specs/auto-scaling.md spec
